Distribution, habitat, and ecology.
Cobitis xui
is found in the Buquan River in Rong’an County, Guangxi , China , Youjiang basin, belonging to the Pearl River drainage ( Fig. 6 ). At the relevant section of the Buquan River, the current was medium to fast, the river width was between 25‒60 m , and the maximum depth was approximately three meters, with the river bed composed of cobbles and gravel. The following fish species co-exist with
C. xui
at the type locality:
Schistura fasciolata (Nichols & Pope)
;
Misgurnus anguillicaudatus (Cantor)
;
Opsariichthys bidens Günther
;
Pseudorasbora parva (Temminck & Schlegel)
;
Squalidus argentatus (Sauvage & Dabry de Thiersant)
;
Acheilognathus tonkinensis (Vaillant)
;
Puntius semifasciolatus (Günther)
;
Spinibarbus denticulatus (Oshima)
;
Spinibarbus caldwelli (Nichols)
;
Rectoris posehensis Lin
;
Osteochilus salsburyi Nichols & Pope
;
Cirrhinus molitorella (Valenciennes)
;
Cyprinus carpio Linnaeus
;
Carassius auratus (Linnaeus)
;
Silurus asotus Linnaeus
and
Clarias fuscus Lacepède.
